a woman is fuming because school officials 
suspended her 8yearold daughter for three days for bringing an 
unopened can of beer to showandtell 
i am furious melissa woodfin said monday i have no 
problem with them having a policy but you cant treat a 
thirdgrader the way you would a teenager 
mrs woodfins daughter haley also must undergo counseling for 
bringing the can of billy beer to school last week 
the beer named for president carters late brother is no 
longer made and unopened cans are considered collectors items 
officials at skipwith elementary school in suburban henrico 
county said the suspension is consistent with their strict drug and 
substance abuse policy 
superintendent william c bosher jr acknowledged that the 
suspension of an elementary school pupil is highly unusual but he 
said the issue is serious 
suspending young people is not what we are about bosher 
said but we want to help young people understand that alcohol 
and drugs are not appropriate 
but mrs woodfin said the punishment did not fit the crime 
my daughter has been treated unfairly she said she has 
lost three days of school with no right to make up the work 
according to the policy 
mrs woodfin said her daughter removed the can of beer from a 
display case at home and took it to school 
she took it for showandtell mrs woodfin said she 
didnt run into a closet and pop it open 
in addition to the suspension police were notified that the 
girl was in illegal possession of an alcoholic beverage 
sgt james price said the girl would be referred to juvenile 
proceedings which is nothing more than a counseling session 
mrs woodfin said the can of billy beer was returned to her by 
police and is back in the display case where it will remain 
haley was back in school monday after serving her suspension 
