a new prosecutor was named monday to retry 
raymond buckey on molestation and conspiracy charges in the 
mcmartin preschool case and district attorney ira reiner said many 
of the charges could be dropped 
deputy district attorney joe martinez replaced lael rubin and 
roger gunson according to a statement issued by reiners office 
rubin and gunson prosecuted buckey 31 and his 63yearold 
mother peggy mcmartin buckey on molestation and conspiracy 
charges a superior court jury acquitted the pair last month of 52 
counts but deadlocked on 13 additional counts against raymond 
buckey 
superior court judge william pounders scheduled a new trial for 
march 9 
reiner said monday the number of charges against buckey probably 
would be reduced because at least two potential witnesses both 
children have balked at the prospect of taking the stand 
the prosecution may ask that up to eight of the 13 counts be 
dismissed he said 
his office listed 17 potential witnesses for the trial 
including all five children named in the charges relatives and 
doctors 
reiner said the list could change 
of the five children named in the remaining counts two did not 
testify at the original trial the youngsters now range in age from 
11 to 14 
if convicted on all 13 counts the maximum sentence buckey could 
receive would be 36 years in prison reiner said 
if convicted of fewer charges buckey could go free because he 
already spent five years behind bars the equivalent of a 10year 
sentence while awaiting trial 
buckey was released on his own recognizance pending the new 
trial 
pounders has said the facts involved in the remaining 13 counts 
mitigate in favor of a long second trial but reiner said 
monday his office hoped to try the case in three months 
defense attorneys and parents of children who attended the 
manhattan beach preschool criticized rubin and gunsons handling of 
the original case the longest costliest criminal proceeding in 
us history 
both rubin and gunson requested reassignment before verdicts 
were announced last month they will assist martinez in the 
transition reiner said 
