<TEXT>
in an attack that appeared 
premeditated about 200 youths in a troubled largely black 
district of liverpool rammed a police patrol car with a stolen car 
then hurled stones at police authorities said 
the youths also set fire to private cars in monday nights 
rioting and threw stones at firefighters who arrived to battle the 
blazes the police said 
the district toxteth was the scene of widespread rioting in 
1981 and was among three largely black innercity districts 
including handsworth in birmingham in central england and tottenham 
in london hit by riots in the fall of 1985 
police refused to speculate on the cause of monday nights 
violence in the northwestern port city 
they said in a statement that trouble flared when white officers 
went to investigate reports of black youths in toxteth arming 
themselves with bricks 
two officers who arrived in a patrol car had the car repeatedly 
rammed by a stolen car and faced a barrage of rocks the statement 
said it said police believed the attack was premeditated 
the statement said two police vans were also damaged in the 
violence and three privately owned autos set on fire it said the 
youths threw stones at firemen who arrived to put out the flames 
police reinforcements arrived and drove the attackers off while 
a police helicopter with a powerful spotlight flew overhead 
one police officer was reported to have received a minor eye 
injury when hit by a stone 
police said nobody was arrested 
superintendent bernard keegan subdivisional police commander 
for toxteth said i appeal to all parents teachers and local 
community leaders to help me in preventing this outrageous behavior 
by misguided youths 
in the violence in 1981 and 1985 black youths said the cause 
was police harassment drug dealing and other street crime is 
widespread in the area and there is often violence when police 
arrest suspects 
social workers say the underlying causes of the rioting in 1981 
and 1985 were high unemployment among young blacks poor housing 
and other social ills 
