communities and society before signing on the dotted line a report 
recommended today 
the report ethical considerations in corporate takeovers 
released by the woodstock theological center at georgetown 
university suggested executives consider ethical questions while 
making deals 
the questions range from are the terms of the transaction 
consistent with the reasonable interests obligations and 
expectations of participants to will the transaction reward 
productive effort innovation and leadership 
the report summing up two years of conferences with prominent 
members of the financial industry government and academia seeks 
to offer an evaluation and recommendations for ethical conduct in 
the financial industry the rev james l connor director of the 
woodstock center said in the foreword 
the report notes corporations do not exist in isolation 
they must be a constructive part of the larger society in 
which they operate and even shareholders who seek solely to 
maximize their own profits will as a practical matter have to 
take into account the interests of workers customers and 
communities without whom the corporation would not exist it 
says 
