<TEXT>
reforms in the soviet union since mikhail s 
gorbachev took power on march 11 1985 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
july 1986 communist party central committee says local 
parliaments will take more responsibility 
june 1987 first experimental contested elections held in some 
local districts 
june 1988 special party conference approves sweeping political 
reform promising shift of power from party to government and a new 
legal system totalitarianism is rejected gorbachev suggests each 
local party leader should seek and win election to the 
corresponding government post 
october 1988 constitutional amendments proposed to change the 
rubberstamp parliament to a real nearly fulltime legislature and 
provide for contested elections 
march 1989 first contested elections for parliament result in 
humiliating defeats for dozens of communist leaders across the 
country 
may 1989 first congress of peoples deputies opens and new 
parliamentarians enthrall the country with their critical speeches 
july 1989 soviet unions first parliamentary opposition the 
interregional group takes form 
december 1989 lithuania approves multiparty system on its 
territory later in the month lithuanian communists create first 
split in the party by voting to break off and form independent 
communist party 
jan 13 1990 gorbachev on a visit to lithuania drops his 
opposition to a multiparty system 
jan 21 reform communists meet in moscow to write alternative 
party platform and threaten to split off into a new party unless 
reforms are made 
sunday hundreds of thousands march through moscow to demand 
democratic reform 
monday gorbachev asks communist party leadership to give up its 
exclusive hold on power 
