<TEXT>
after months of combing want ads and 
finding he was too old or too qualified for academic positions 
romanian defector paul petrescu says he was glad to find work as 
groundskeeper at a country inn 
the job which sometimes means shoveling snow and sweeping 
halls might seem like a comedown for a man with two doctorates 
five languages and an authoritative knowledge of romanian folk art 
but the 69yearold defector is happy to have the work 
it is very healthy exercise said petrescu who has 
doctorates in sociology and political science from the university 
of bucharest but now calls himself dean of the eightman grounds 
crew i was a soccer player in my time i feel like im on a 
sports team we are friends 
and despite the revolution in his homeland he plans to stay 
petrescu and his wife juliana decided to try to leave romania 
three years ago the plan was for petrescu to leave first 
establish himself in the west and then send for his wife and son 
when he was allowed to join a lecture tour in switzerland 
petrescu took the opportunity to slip into the west german embassy 
and was granted a visa through his contacts in that country but 
the west german government was reluctant to issue visas for 
petrescus family so 11 months ago he applied for political asylum 
in the united states 
he came to stockbridge in the berkshire hills by way of his 
friendship with local resident john c ffrench who met petrescu 32 
years ago at a traveling romanian folk art exhibit in india 
