<TEXT>
west german chancellor helmut kohl called 
today for immediate talks with east germany on combining their 
currencies in an effort to stop people from fleeing the 
economically crippled communist nation 
kohl made the announcement during a meeting with leading 
politicians of his christian democratic union and the allied 
christian social union he said details will be worked out when 
east german premier hans modrow visits bonn next week 
discussions on using west germanys robust currency to revive 
replace or reinforce the comparatively puny east german mark have 
grown more intense as the communist countrys economy nears 
collapse 
earlier today the influential president of west germanys 
central bank said it was too early for a monetary union that would 
make the west german mark east germanys currency 
deutsche bundesbank president karl otto poehl also said he is 
opposed to the idea of introducing the west german mark as a 
parallel official currency in east germany he spoke to reporters 
after talks in east berlin with horst kaminski president of the 
east german central bank 
the east german economy has been crippled by a continuing exodus 
of skilled workers to west germany strikes and abstenteeism more 
than 50000 east germans moved west in january alone joining more 
than 340000 others who resettled in west germany last year 
east german economic output is expected to drop by between 4 
percent and 5 percent this year the government says east germany 
has asked west germany for immediate aid of up to 88 billion but 
a west german spokesman has called the request unrealistic 
east germans are impatient with the pace of reform and have been 
drawn to the west by the prospect of earning valuable west german 
marks instead of the inconvertible east german marks 
poehl said the east german mark would have to be made gradually 
convertible before monetary reform is achieved 
west german economics minister helmut haussmann was quoted as 
saying today that the west german mark could become a parallel 
currency in east germany as early as this year if the east 
german government is willing to take such a step 
haussmann said the step was needed to stem the exodus to the 
west according to the neue osnabruecker zeitung newspaper 
but central bank officials have taken a far more cautious 
approach on monetary union stressing that major economic reforms 
must be undertaken first by the east german government 
in davos switzerland wolfgang berghofer mayor of the east 
german city of dresden today proposed making the east german mark 
convertible as the only way to avoid a complete collapse of the 
east german economy 
berghofer said the quickest route to make the east german 
currency convertible would be to link it to the west german mark at 
a fixed rate of four east german marks to one west german one 
speaking to reporters berghofer said hopelessness and 
desperation prevailed in east germany and warned that the country 
only has a matter of days to give its citizens a measure of 
reassurance to avert an even larger exodus in the spring 
berghofer was in davos attending an international economic forum 
late monday about 100000 people rallied in leipzig with many 
speakers and demonstrators calling for quick reunification the 
official news agency adn reported 
adn said a group of ultrarightist republicans from west germany 
joined the rally marching with their arms raised in the nazi 
salute 
