significantly warm the earth by the middle of the next century 
what were hearing is talk of another year of waiting i 
expected a lot more concern about the global warming problem 
said rafe pomerance of the world resources institute 
bush speaking to the 60nation intergovernmental panel on 
climate change said our policies must be consistent with 
economic growth he complained that in some areas of the debate 
over the greenhouse effect politics and opinion have outpaced 
the science 
our goal continues to be matching policy commitments to 
emerging scientific knowledge and a reconciling of environmental 
protection to the continued benefits of economic development the 
