and outmoded strategic analysis which holds the maintenance of 
close ties with china to be the key to any successful containment 
of soviet expansionism 
it said such a policy has reverted to a shabby double standard 
insofar as the question of human rights in china 
the asia watch report follows the completion of a study by the 
us state department on human rights abuses in china according to 
press reports the study says the massacre in beijing and 
subsequent crackdown violated almost every internationally 
recognized human right 
the state department report will be released later this month 
