bin akao an activist in japans rightist movement 
died of heart failure tuesday at the age of 91 
for 35 years akao was a fixture in central tokyos ginza 
district where he preached to passing shoppers and office workers 
through a loudspeaker from a truck painted with such slogans as 
japanese unite under the emperor 
akao a native of nagoya in western japan started as a 
socialist activist when he organized a farmers union after 
graduating from junior high school but he became a rightist after 
he was jailed in 1925 for his union activism 
akao was elected to the house of representatives the lower 
house of parliament from a tokyo district in 1942 but said he was 
expelled in 1943 because he opposed japans attack on the united 
states he said he called instead for japan to join with the 
western powers in a move to crush the soviet union 
after the war the allied occupation forces banned him from 
holding public office when the ban ended in 1951 he established 
the anticommunist great japan patriots party of which he was 
president the rightist political organization has a membership of 
150 in japan according to national police agency figures 
akao also was a leader in the nationwide rightist movement 
comprising 840 groups with 120000 members 
after the war he ran unsuccessfully more than 20 times for 
parliament and other offices 
akao was believed associated with a series of rightwing 
terrorist acts in postwar japan including the 1960 assassination 
of then japan socialist party chairman inejiro asanuma by one of 
akaos followers akao had a record of 25 arrests for violent 
political activities 
on his sound truck flanked by several flags of japan the 
united states and anticommunist taiwan akao would call in his 
gravelly voice for a strengthening of the usjapan military 
alliance and japans emperor system and the toppling of the 
communist government of the soviet union 
in some of his speeches he referred to leaders of japans 
conservative governing party the liberal democrats as idiots 
and moneygrubbers after a series of money scandals 
his party headquarters was decorated with portraits of emperors 
buddha jesus christ the chinese philospher confucius and otoya 
yamaguchi the 17yearold who stabbed asanuma 
he spoke of hoping to unite confucianism buddhism communism 
and christianity into a culture of unity and peace japans emperor 
would be a suitable leader he said 
