from lung cancer and cigarette advertising is partly to blame 
the american cancer society said tuesday 
in its annual cancer facts and figures the society predicts 
92000 men will die this year of lung cancer down from 93000 last 
year and the first decline since the projections began in 1953 
thats because men have been quitting smoking over the last two 
decades first younger men and now all age groups said cancer 
society spokeswoman joann schellenbach that is translating into 
fewer cases of lung cancer 
about 50000 women will die of lung cancer up from 49000 last 
year the organization said 
schellenbach said women also are starting to give up smoking 
but their health trend hasnt caught up to mens yet because men 
started smoking at the turn of the century and women started 
smoking in the 1930s 
in addition she said while many older women are trying to 
quit many younger ones dont because theyre afraid of gaining 
weight 
