conference but im angry that we have to be here at all 
mrs bradys husband was severely wounded during an 
assassination attempt on president reagan in 1981 
the bill supported by mrs brady would ban the import 
manufacture sale and possession of the 14 weapons it was approved 
last year by the senate judiciary committee and is awaiting action 
by the full senate she called on senate leaders to call it up to 
the floor this week and let the american public know where their 
senators stand 
gun owner support groups have opposed the legislation on the 
grounds that semiautomatic weapons one pull of the trigger fires 
one round are essentially the same as many hunting rifles and 
would force many sportsmen to give up their weapons 
rabbi lynne landsberg assistant director of the religious 
action center of reform judaism said at the news conference we 
cannot begin to curb crime and the epidemic of random violence 
which plagues our cities while we continue to legitimize the 
wholesale arming of ordinary citizens including the mentally 
defective and the street gangs 
warren eisenberg director of the international council of bnai 
brith said his organization does not believe the bill would 
interfere with the legitimate activities of sportsmen 
in an age when hate criminals and narcoterrorists use assault 
weapons to commit their crimes it is ridiculous to try to defend 
certain categories of domestic and imported weapons as sporting 
equipment eisenberg said 
the american federation of teachers distributed a statement 
supporting the bill as a positive first step and saying 
because of the access people have to semiautomatic assault 
weapons we have to add violent crime to the list of problems 
facing our children we should be doing everything in our power to 
insure that american students are protected from violence 
dr john seward member and past chairman of the american 
medical association council on legislation urged approval of the 
legislation saying as a physician and a county coroner in 
northwestern illinois i have seen firsthand the devastating 
wounds inflicted by assault weapons fired during violent crimes 
robert z alpern director of the washington office of the 
unitarian universalist association said passage of the bill 
would be a small step toward limiting the supply of 
semiautomatic weapons that have taken an unconscionable toll of 
human lives and terrorized our nation 
stanley chauvin president of the american bar association 
urged action on the bill to prevent a permanent militarylike 
escalation of drug crime in our nation 
jim moran mayor alexandria va and chairman of the human 
development policy committee of the national league of cities said 
he spoke for the bill on the basis of nlc policy which i also 
happen to fervently and wholeheartedly endorse as a mayor as a 
citizen of my community and as a worried parent as well 
the 14 weapons are the mac10 and mac11 steyr aug colt ar15 
and colt car15 uzi carbine and uzi pistol beretta ar70 galil 
avtomat kalashnikovs fnfnc fnfallar striker 12 streetsweeper 
