<TEXT>
interim president ion iliescu 
registered the former ruling national salvation front on tuesday to 
run in the may 20 elections and a top aide said iliescu will be 
its presidential candidate 
the front unelected and ruling by decree since longtime 
communist dictator nicolae ceausescu was toppled and executed in 
december is considered the frontrunner in the race against 29 
political parties 
our candidate for president will be mr iliescu thats for 
sure thats what everyone wants said dan radulescu chief of 
the fronts commission for press and public relations 
