multiparty elections since world war ii are held in may the new 
national unity council will meet for the first time friday 
in its platform released tuesday the front said its aim is 
realization in romania of a democratic society based on political 
pluralism the separation of powers in the state the assurance of 
liberty and human dignity 
the front said it also sought to guarantee the inviolability 
of human rights the respecting of the rights and liberties of all 
national minorities the guarantee of freedom of religion 
another platform goal is creation of a modern national 
economy based on efficiency and individual as well as collective 
initiative 
roman said romania was moving slowly toward a market economy and 
faced two major economic problems that it produced only basic 
products and that its largest industries had far greater capacity 
than the country needs 
the platform included membership guidelines and an outline of 
the partys structure from villages on up it bars from membership 
anyone convicted of crimes against the revolution 
the platform made no mention of the communist party last month 
the front announced it would outlaw the party then it decided to 
submit the question to a referendum only to cancel the vote a 
short time later 
asked in the interview whether the communist party was dead for 
all practical purposes roman replied the communist party 
doesnt exist any more practically it was a selfdissolution 
he said the front and every political party had former 
communists as members 
sources in the front speaking on condition of anonymity 
meanwhile said tourism minister mihai lupoi had resigned radulescu 
said he could not confirm the resignation 
