nearly 11 million was spent on the eight races there were 41 
initial candidates in the eight elections with the 16 who survived 
to participate in the final headtohead contests accounting for 
89 million of the spending total 
the national parties and their state affiliates invested heavily 
in those races with total expenditures by the major parties 
reaching neatly 12 million 
