<TEXT>
jurors in the assault and conspiracy trial of 
reputed mob boss john gotti concluded their first day of 
deliberations tuesday after listening again to 11 tapes that are 
the prosecutions key evidence 
the jury retired at about 715 pm and was to resume 
deliberations wednesday morning 
law enforcement officers secretly recorded a dozen tapes of 
conversations at gottis hangout in the borough of queens and in 
the visiting room of a jail 
among the conversations jurors heard again were one in which 
gotti allegedly says were gonna gonna bust him up which the 
prosecution says is a reference to a former union leader and 
another in which members of the westies gang allegedly say they 
shot the man as a favor to gotti 
the defense has ridiculed the tapes as inaudible and claims 
prosecutors transcribed them to suit their theory that gotti had 
john f oconnor shot 
as the jury began deliberations earlier in the day acting 
justice edward mclaughlin told the four alternate jurors they would 
be held in court custody and he could not tell them why 
a court source said the alternates were being held at least 
until tomorrow and maybe longer to minimize chances of their 
being found and bothered for information about the 12 main jurors 
since their swearingin about three weeks ago all the jurors 
have been sequestered to shield them from publicity and possible 
jurytampering court officials estimate it costs 1200 a day to 
feed house and transport them 
about two hours after getting the case the jurors sent a note 
requesting a rereading of the definition of firstdegree 
intentional assault the first count on their verdict sheet they 
then began rehearing the tapes 
gotti 49 and his codefendant anthony tony lee guerrieri 
61 are accused of commissioning the westies a gang from 
manhattans hells kitchen district to shoot oconnor former vice 
president of carpenters union local 608 on may 7 1986 oconnor 
was shot in the buttocks and survived 
assistant district attorney michael cherkasky said gotti 
alleged boss of the gambino crime family arranged the shooting 
because oconnor ordered goons to trash bankers and brokers a 
mobrun restaurant in lower manhattan that was being built with 
nonunion labor 
the judge told the jurors that to convict they must find the 
prosecution proved the specific elements of the crime charged in 
the trial and not simply that gotti and his codefendant might be 
members of organized crime 
he also reminded them that the prosecutions key witness former 
westies member and confessed killer james mcelroy 45 testified he 
had previously lied under oath the judge told the jurors it was up 
to them to decide whether they believe mcelroy was testifying 
truthfully against gotti 
just before the jurors left to deliberate mclaughlin admonished 
them 
the person that you were when you left your apartment those 
weeks ago is the person youre supposed to be in the jury room 
he said do not become somebody else dont turn the jury room 
into the twilight zone dont expect divine intervention 
you do not have to answer to anybody but yourselves regarding 
the verdict mclaughlin said if you can look at yourself in 
the mirror every day for the rest of your life and say i 
conscientiously followed the law and called it as i saw it then 
whatever your verdict turns out to be it will have been the 
correct one 
in closing arguments monday defense lawyers bruce cutler and 
gerald shargel said gotti was being persecuted because of his 
reputation 
when the smoke clears you will realize one thing that there 
is no proof let alone proof beyond a reasonable doubt that john 
gotti and anthony guerrieri had john oconnor shot shargel said 
the judge told the jurors the charges they are to consider 
intentional first and seconddegree assault reckless first and 
seconddegree assault fourthdegree conspiracy a felony and 
fifthdegree conspiracy a misdemeanor 
if convicted gotti could face 25 years to life in prison as a 
persistent felon because of convictions in 1969 and 1974 
