the senate tuesday defeated an attempt to 
strip federal funds from a national school teacher certification 
board setting the stage for passage of a nearly 15 billion 
educational improvement bill 
by a 6435 vote lawmakers turned back an attempt by sen jesse 
helms rnc and others to strike from the excellence in 
education act a provision giving federal money to the panel 
critics argued that it would give the federal government too great 
a say in setting teacher standards 
supporters of the provision tacked onto sweeping education 
legislation president bush sent to capitol hill in april 1989 said 
