john marin is an artist who helped give credibility to 
watercolor and remove it as the stepchild of oil 
through his landscapes treescapes cityscapes and seascapes of 
new york maine and new mexico he demonstrated a brilliant use of 
color and form running shapes and lines into ideas and form 
for 40 years marin contributed to modern art a retrospective 
of his work is now at the national gallery of art in washington 
through april 15 
there are close to 150 works in selections and 
transformations the art of john marin including watercolors and 
oil paintings 
marin was born in rutherford nj in 1870 he died in 1953 
two of his finest watercolors are wave on rock 1937 and 
related to brooklyn bridge 1928 
in boston the museum of fine arts has opened monet in the 
90s the series paintings 
monet the leading french impressionist is known to have done 
218 series paintings all but 12 during the 1890s when he was 
in his 50s 
he chose 16 subjects some for their historical or cultural 
significance among the works were 30 paintings each of grain 
stacks and the rouen cathedral 24 paintings of poplars and 18 of 
the japanese bridge over his waterlily garden at giverny 
there are 86 in the exhibition more than twice the number monet 
ever showed at one time the works are on loan from all over the 
world including leningrad paris tokyo and boston the show runs 
through april 29 before going to the art institute of chicago from 
may 19 through aug 12 and at the royal academy in london from 
sept 7 through dec 9 
here is a list of exhibits and shows in some american museums 
and galleries 
