<TEXT>
phil collins writes his album titles last to 
reflect the the mood of the music on the album 
his new album is but seriously the first single 
another day in paradise is about the homeless there also are 
songs about famine and apartheid 
in a recent interview collins recalled his last solo album 
no jacket required in 1985 
apart from the little story of a chicago hotel that wouldnt 
let me into the bar because i wasnt wearing a jacket i thought 
the album was hotter more danceable material than my previous 
two he said i wanted to do something now that had a little 
bit more depth to it for a variety of reasons 
one is that it follows collins acting and songs in the movie 
buster a film about the great train robbery 
not a light subject but the way the film treated that subject 
it was kind of a romantic comedy he said that was fine 
because it was an acting role when i got involved with the music 
i think the results to the casual person in the street were maybe a 
little light 
i was working with lamont dozier a hero of mine and it was a 
film project it didnt bother me a groovy kind of love was a 
60s song i think a lot of people thought it was a phil collins 
solo project and felt i was getting very very light that wasnt 
where i was coming from 
i thought let me put that right with my next album that 
was one of the reasons the content of some songs was a little 
different for me 
most of the album reflects romantic and other individual 
concerns i think theyre my best collection of songs since face 
value he said that was his first solo album in 1981 followed 
a year later by hello i must be going 
after all ive done it is nice to know the best is still yet 
to come really collins said the album was great fun to 
write not having done it for five years many of them came easily 
there was a lot to come out 
hell tour until september id like to do another film the 
end of 1990 weve got to do a genesis album the beginning of 1991 
i dont want to get involved with a big tour again so soon after 
the solo tour 
by that time ill be almost 40 id like to do another album 
maybe id like to concentrate on films i think well tour with 
genesis because its part of what we do it wont be if i can 
help it anywhere near as long as genesis last tour which was 10 
months 
the gigs become the most important part of the day everything 
else tends to be very boring one hotel after another one plane 
after another i never get bored with the gigs theyre always 
different i can hea people say hes bored with firstclass 
hotels it does get boring id rather be at home doing the 
shopping 
speaking of boredom collins said there is always a risk that 
people get bored with phil collins that reached a peak in 198586 
when we had five top 5 singles with no jacket required and 
genesis invisible touch had five top 5 the voice was constantly 
on the radio there was a severe danger of overkill which is why i 
took a year away from music and did buster 
people still played the records on the radio he said the 
thing that sticks in my mind is a guitar player said milwaukee had 
a guaranteed phil collinsfree weekend when radio stations 
guarantee not to play you you know youre in trouble 
i dont want to not work because people play the records too 
much 
some of but seriously was recorded in los angeles david 
crosby who sings on another day in paradise and horn players 
collins wanted to use live there jill collins is from los angeles 
their daughter lily 10 months will go on the 1990 tour and his 
older children a daughter 17 and son 13 will join them in 
australia on their spring break 
while recording collins said there are technical things that 
can thicken the voice such as echoes 
theyre security blankets some singers use to mask 
inadequacies he said i was guilty of that my voice became a 
bit of a sound rather than just the voice i think my singing has 
gotten better over the last few years i expose it more on this 
album i use less effects 
since buster which came out in late 1988 collins produced 
three songs on stephen bishops album and played on woman in 
chains tears for fears current single 
eric clapton who is one of my best friends was making his 
album around the same time i did my album he played on mine i 
played on his collins said 
he didnt expect his success and it has always surprised him 
if you take things for granted thats when the trouble starts 
people say why is it what you do appeals to other people i 
have no idea if i knew then id probably screw it up he said 
maybe i write lyrics that are very direct people understand 
them and relate to them maybe thats why what happens happens 
apart from that you do it to please yourself first if other 
people like it thats great 
