<TEXT>
ken kesey took 12 writers from the 
university of oregon master of fine arts program into his house 
then showed them the tricks of writing a novel by having them 
produce one 
like many first efforts this one started awkwardly with kesey 
knocking himself cold on a window frame trying to break into the 
house he uses in eugene because he forgot the key 
but the ending was a happy one viking penguin bought the 
manuscript and in january released caverns by ou levon 
taken from uo novel spelled backwards 
caverns is set in 1934 chosen by kesey because it is the 
year before his own birth the psychedelic pioneer of the 1960s is 
the author of one flew over the cuckoos nest and sometimes a 
great notion 
the story for caverns describes how carnival huckster 
charles oswald loach is released from san quentin where he is 
serving 20 years for murder to lead an expedition aboard an army 
surplus field ambulance to a mysterious cave purported to contain a 
wild mix of prehistoric paintings that challenge the basic tenets 
of anthropology 
we didnt set a high standard kesey said of the book which 
was published in paperback on soft paper to give it a pulp fiction 
feel if we had decided to write thomas pynchons gravitys 
rainbow we would be still writing or we would have stopped 
writing 
kesey had everyone develop a character they evolved into loach 
his desert rat brother a girl who grew up in loachs carnival act 
a white supremacist brick maker a sailor an anthropologist a 
priest an alcoholic newspaperman a wouldbe movie producer and 
two oldmaid spiritualist sisters 
unlike the collaborative novels in which writers have taken a 
chapter to themselves this one was written with everyone pulling a 
piece of each chapter out of a hat then getting 30 minutes to 
write it afterward the book went through two revisions 
if youve got a good point guard and two power forwards and 
keep moving the ball around somebodys going to score kesey 
said 
the method also minimized individual style and the shark attacks 
so common in writing workshops 
you were in fine shape if you started out the chapter said 
h highwater powers you could lay it out if you were the last 
person you had to adjust you had to think on your feet 
kesey said that was one of the great lessons of the class 
in the hard and sticky and dry parts that you come to in your 
life or your work all you have to do is put one foot in front of 
the other and pretty soon you find yourself in places you didnt 
expect to be he said theres no way you can teach that you 
can only learn that 
he recalled one discussion when someone complained that the plot 
had taken an unbelievable turn 
i said thats the job of the writer kesey said weve 
got to take the square peg and jam it into the round hole 
the life of it comes from making people believe that these 
people are drawing breath and standing up casting shadows and 
living lives and feeling agonies 
and thats a trick its a glorious trick and its a trick 
that you can be taught its not just a thing that comes from 
the muses 
</TEXT>
