flos biggest worry was would the quilting fall apart barb 
says 
who is there to replace the replacements 
barb sighs if we dont get young blood like all things it 
will die 
the morning wears the chatter slows the women roll up the ends 
of the finished spread as they work scooting their chairs forward 
and inward it is godawful cold outside and getting worse as the 
day develops but in the warm basement the women of st marys keep 
sewing knees to knees around an evershrinking quilt 
