<TEXT>
like many middleaged and older americans 
carolyn connor was raised to believe that nice people didnt get 
divorced 
but at 49 shes been married divorced remarried and widowed 
society raised me to think it was an embarrassment to get a 
divorce but he was an alcoholic when i got a little money from 
my grandfathers estate it gave me the guts to leave said 
connor who was divorced at 33 
it really makes me feel sorry for people who dont have the 
money 
sociologists say that while divorce rates have stabilized for 
younger women they are increasing for older women and newly 
divorced middleaged and older women have a harder time financially 
than widows or those divorced early 
almost everyone recognized there was a tremendous increase in 
divorce rates since the 1960s said peter uhlenberg a university 
of north carolina sociologist divorce is concentrated in younger 
women most occur before age 40 women in later life those who 
are old now have not been affected by these changes were trying 
to anticipate what happens when women in their younger adult years 
hit their 60s and 70s 
uhlenberg and his associates teresa cooney now at the 
university of delaware and robert boyd presently a graduate 
student at the university of south carolina used data from the 
us census vital statistics and current population survey for 
their study published in the january edition of the journal of 
gerontology social sciences 
they found that one woman in eight will have her first marriage 
end in divorce after she reaches age 40 and the probability of 
remarriage is slim decreasing rapidly with age in 1985 for 
example researchers found fewer than three out of 100 divorced 
women aged 45 to 64 remarried 
there are competing explanations for why more older women are 
getting divorced and remaining unmarried its becoming more 
feasible for women to support themselves outside of marriage there 
are more work opportunities the age before marriage has gone up 
the whole idea of being married is becoming less likeable after 
doing it once uhlenberg said 
the economic status family relationships social support and 
emotional stability of recently divorced middleaged and older 
women vary dramatically from those comparably married widowed or 
longtermed divorced women 
much more often a widowed woman will have a house which is a 
major asset going into old age uhlenberg said widowed women are 
also more likely to have their husbands pension as a source of 
income but for divorced older women the social implications are 
very different 
a widowed woman is much more likely to be living independently 
and not working he said divorced women are compensating 
economically by sharing their living expenses and working 
it takes a while to recover financially from divorce said 
ms connor who has worked as a secretary for three years to 
supplement her late husbands disabled veterans benefits and at 
the time i divorced they didnt really enforce child support i 
had my husband arrested twice for not paying and all they did was 
put him in jail overnight and then let him go 
the picture becomes more bleak for older minority women 
uhlenberg said 
divorce rates are significantly higher for blacks we know 
that the economic implications are about what they are for white 
women its just that more black women will experience economic 
disadvantages 
another factor affecting divorce rates is the increased 
acceptability of single mothers and cohabitation before marriage 
he said and the more these types of families exist the less 
likely children of such groups are to be socialized into the 
pattern of stable family relationships 
what were doing now is looking at one of the implications of 
divorce on older men which will be published this month he 
said specifically the impact of divorce on older men and their 
relationship with their children 
weve found that older divorced men are much less likely to 
have contact with their adult children they report the 
relationship to be less satisfactory 
for women we find a greater impact on an economic level 
while for men the implication would be in terms of social 
support 
