<TEXT>
come on over for a bite of supper 
this is the kind of entertaining that is doable 
nothing fancy mind you but an easy inexpensive casserole 
dinner with fresh seasonal greens a crusty bread and dessert 
it can be a pot luck where the host andor hostess prepare the 
main dish and friends bring separate components that make up the 
rest of the meal or if you do it all it can take as little as 
two hours the casserole can go stove top to table top in 30 
minutes and its easy to wash fresh greens for salad whisk 
together a light vinaigrette spread whole wheat baguettes with 
herb butter and whip up a simple dessert 
yet what i so often hear from friends in my travels around the 
country these days is now that the kids have grown up we dont 
entertain much any more or i seldom entertain now that im 
alone this is the very time when entertaining should be at the 
top of our priority list 
whether weve moved to another area from a house to an 
apartment or stayed put entertaining is a conduit through which 
we can share friendship and in opening ourselves up to each other 
we gain perspective encouragement and succor 
people love to go to each others houses and informality is 
often appreciated theres no need to put on the ritz with a 
threecourse dinner and rich dessert light simple food is 
preferred especially at this time of our lives when too many 
calories and too much fat can ruin our efforts to keep fit 
the number of people four or six five or seven singles and 
couples mix and match in both ages and interests 
the cost of this king of entertaining can be as little as 5 a 
person and it enriches our lives beyond measure 
i like to entertain once aa month my friend mary rommer 
says but i dont want to go to that much bother so i make it 
really easy on myself 
use pots platters and ovenware that can come to table plates 
and glasses that can take the heat of the dishwasher runners and 
placemats that dont need ironing foods that dont need looking 
after and casseroles that can sit around in the oven or on top of 
the stove or a big kettle 
i serve just the first time around and then guests can help 
themselves 
heres one of my favorite casserole dinners 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
2 tablespoons butter 
2 tablespoons olive oil 
2 large onions peeled and finely chopped 
2 medium leeks thoroughly rinsed and cut into 1inch pieces 
2 cloves garlic peeled and finely chopped 
3 whole chicken breasts about 1 pound each bones intact 
rinsed skinned and patted dry 
3 medium carrots peeled and cut into 1inch slices 
1 16ounce can of small white beans 
1 16ounce can of pinto beans 
1 10ounce package frozen lima beans defrosted 
1 tablespoon chili sauce or 1 tablespoon tomato paste 
1 tablespoon dried leaf thyme 
3 cups canned beef or chicken broth 
3 medium yellow squash trimmed and cut into inchthick slices 
salt and pepper to taste 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
1 melt the 2 tablespoons of butter in a skillet over medium 
heat add the onions leeks and garlic and saute until translucent 
about 57 minutes with a slotted spoon remove the cooked 
vegetables and set aside 
2 heat the 2 tablespoons of olive oil and saute the chicken 
breasts about 5 minutes on each side until browned 
3 in a 6quart casserole combine the sauteed chicken and 
onions leeks garlic carrots chili sauce thyme and broth and 
simmer about 15 minutes 
4 add the beans and yellow squash and cook 10 minutes longer 
5 with a slotted spoon transfer the chicken to a cutting board 
and bone the chicken in strips then return to casserole 
6 serve hot at the table or cool you may freeze at this 
point and refrigerate covered 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
2 bunches of watercress rinsed stems removed and patted dry 
2 bunches of arugula rinsed and patted dry 
13 cup olive oil 
13 cup red wine vinegar 
1 tablespoon fresh lemon juice 
1 teaspoons dijonstyle mustard 
freshly ground pepper to taste 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
1 in a medium salad bowl combine the greens 
2 in a small bowl whisk together the remaining ingredients 
3 refrigerate the greens and dressing in separate covered bowls 
4 just before serving toss the greens with the dressing 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
1 envelope unflavored gelatin 
2 cans 1 pound each whole peeled apricots drained juice 
reserved use enough apricots to make 1 cups and cups of juice 
and reserve the remainder for another use 
1 quart vanilla ice cream softened 
garnish strawberries or kumquats 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
1 in a medium saucepan over low heat warm the apricot juice 
slightly 
2 sprinkle the gelatin over the syrup and heat about 5 minutes 
stirring constantly until the gelatin dissolves 
3 place the apricots in a blender whirl until slightly pureed 
but still with some texture 
4 fold into the ice cream spoon into individual stem glasses 
or into a serving bowl 
5 refrigerate covered for about 3 hours to set 
6 garnish each serving with one large whole strawberry or a 
half kumquat 
</TEXT>
