guilty to six felony counts each of which would carry a maximum 
five years in prison 
the government would recommend to the judge that milken serve 
the counts concurrently for a maximum of five years or the 
equivalent of one felony charge but a judge would not be bound by 
the recommendation none of the six counts would involve 
racketeering which carries a maximum 20year prison term 
assistant us attorney john carroll did not return a call 
seeking comment on the report 
a spokesman for milken said weve never commented and wont 
