<DOCNO> AP900206-0230 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
lotus development corp went to federal court 
today to prove that two competitors copied its popular business 
spreadsheet program in a suit that could clarify copywrite laws for 
computer software 
lotus which says its lawsuit aims to protect computer 
innovations began the case by demonstrating its lotus 123 
program to the court 
using video screens the company showed the basic steps for 
setting up financial statements graphs and mortgage projections by 
inserting numbers into various columns and rows 
lotus filed suit in 1987 against paperback software 
international of berkeley calif and mosaic software of 
cambridge claiming a copyright infringement of the look and 
feel of lotus popular 123 program 
the case centers on what protection should be given to images 
that appear on a computer screen and the commands associated with 
the program known as the user interface 
a lot of people are looking at the case to make a decision on 
the issue said ned saltzberg a boston lawyer and editor of the 
computer law newsletter 
legal experts say the inner workings of the program are 
protected by copyright laws but lotus argues that the computer 
screen display constitutes an expression of an idea and thus falls 
under copyright protection 
lotus is alleging these companies copied keystroke for 
keystroke the spreadsheet modules for 123 said bryan simmons 
a spokesman for the cambridgebased company 
the 123 menus provide users with options such as file 
print copy and combine and keyboard buttons are 
punched to activate those options 
paul gupta a lawyer representing paperback software said 
what appears on a menu does not constitute expression where 
youve got a simple list of words on a screen its not enough to 
call it copyrightable 
gupta said paperback software to some extent had its hands 
tied in the development of its vpplanner spreadsheet program in 
order to make a product that is compatible with lotus 123 the 
company had to use technologies that result in similar computer 
images and commands he said 
where we had the opportunity to make changes we did he 
said 
in fact paperback software says by building on lotus system 
the company was following a pattern in the computer industry in 
which borrowed ideas have led to innovations 
adam osborne president of the company noted that lotus modeled 
123 after a previous program visicalc and he said his firm has 
made further improvements 
they had to hobble us with legal processes he said 
officials at mosaic software were not available for comment 
monday 
but simmons at lotus said a ruling in his companys favor 
would not stifle innovation but would do the opposite 
without the copyright protection an entrepreneur might not 
experiment with new products for fear that a big company will 
swallow up the idea he said 
lotus believes this will encourage innovators to take risks 
simmons said 
also he said companies can use the idea of a business 
spreadsheet but do not need to copy each others material in order 
to compete other spreadsheets such as microsoft excel are very 
different from our product he said 
it comes down to are you building on an idea or building on 
an expression of an idea he said 
lee gesmer a partner with the boston law firm of lucash gesmer 
amp updegrove which publishes the technology law bulletin said he 
expects lotus to win the case based on recent similar decisions 
but perhaps more importantly saltzberg said the case should 
give software designers a better idea of what is and isnt 
permissible 
as long as the rules are clear people can abide by them he 
said 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

