<TEXT>
virgin atlantic airways announced tuesday it is 
introducing completely nonsmoking flights between new york and 
london starting may 18 
virgin owned by british entrepreneur richard branson said it 
is the first airline to offer such service between the two cities 
the airline said increasing passenger demand for smokefree flights 
prompted the move 
other transatlantic carriers are also considering nonsmoking 
flights 
congress passed a bill last november banning smoking on 
virtually all us domestic flights effective feb 25 
international flights however usually offer smoking sections 
this is the first clear alternative to nonsmoking sections 
which are never completely satisfactory for todays 
healthconscious traveler virgin said in a statement 
the airline said it will introduce a second flight between 
newark nj and gatwick airport outside london on thursdays 
fridays saturdays and sundays to accommodate the new nonsmoking 
service virgin will continue to offer smoking and nonsmoking 
sections on its other daily flights to london out of newark and 
john f kennedy international airport in new york 
