as eastern finalizes its reorganization plans we are confident 
that a far more competitive airline will emerge 
eastern management recently proposed to pay unsecured creditors 
only 10 percent of their debts in cash when the airline emerges 
from bankruptcy protection and another 70 percent over the 
following 10 years without interest in return for accepting 
partial repayment texas air would give the unsecured creditors 40 
percent of easterns equity 
in addition preferred shareholders would receive no more than 
10 cents on the dollar in the form of new stock a committee 
representing preferred shareholders attacked the plan 
easterns fourthquarter losses included a special charge of 
1537 million in back pay to some pilots pension curtailment 
costs and legal expenses for the bankruptcy case 
